# Persistence Layer

## Entity Pattern
```java
@Entity
@Table(name = "orders")
@Accessors(chain = true)
@Getter @Setter @NoArgsConstructor @Builder @AllArgsConstructor
@EqualsAndHashCode(onlyExplicitlyIncluded = true)
public class OrderEntity {
    @Id
    @Column(name = "order_id", nullable = false, length = 36)
    @EqualsAndHashCode.Include
    private String id;

    @Version
    @Column(name = "version", nullable = false)
    private Integer version;
}
```
- Column names: `snake_case` | Fields: `camelCase`
- Always use `@Version` for optimistic locking
- String UUIDs for primary keys (length = 36)

## Repository Pattern
```java
@Lazy
public interface OrderRepository extends JpaRepository<OrderEntity, String> {
    @Modifying
    @Query("update OrderEntity o set o.status = ?2 where o.id = ?1")
    void updateStatusById(String id, StatusType status);
}
```
- Extend `JpaRepository<Entity, IdType>` with `@Lazy`
- JPQL preferred over native SQL
- `@Query` + `@Modifying` for update/delete operations

## DAL (Data Access Layer)
```java
@Component @Transactional @Log4j2
public class OrderDal {
    private final OrderRepository repository;
    private final OrderMapper mapper;
}
```

## MapStruct Mappers
```java
@Mapper
public interface OrderMapper {
    OrderMapper MAPPER = Mappers.getMapper(OrderMapper.class);
    Order toOrder(OrderEntity entity);
}
```

## Database Rules
- DDL managed by **Liquibase** — never `ddl-auto`
- PostgreSQL in production, H2 for unit tests

## Liquibase Conventions
```xml
<changeSet id="{module}-{sequence}-{description}" author="developer">
    <addColumn tableName="orders">
        <column name="status" type="VARCHAR(50)" defaultValue="ACTIVE"/>
    </addColumn>
    <rollback>
        <dropColumn tableName="orders" columnName="status"/>
    </rollback>
</changeSet>
```
- **Always include `<rollback>`** for every changeset
- Incremental sequence numbers (001, 002, 003...)
- One logical change per changeset
- Table/column names: `snake_case`
